text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia vassalii is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The spreading rounded shrub typically grows to a height of 0.15 to 0.3 metres (0.5 to 1.0 ft). It blooms from June to July and produces yellow flowers.
